Content:: Tower 185 is a 55-storey, 200 m (660 ft) skyscraper in the Gallus district of Frankfurt, Germany. It is the 4th tallest building in Frankfurt and the 4th tallest in Germany, tied with Main Tower. The anchor tenant of the tower is the German branch office of PricewaterhouseCoopers, which has leased 60,000 m2 (650,000 sq ft). The tower was initially planned to be 185 m (607 ft) with 50 stories; however, when plans changed to increase the height by an additional five floors, its name was not changed.
